Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 68dd075a8ddf644c0056f6ecdb50cd0c4a463f20
Could you also link which daemon implements this interface? Is it already in phosphor-debug-collector?
yes. I will update the commit msg with the same.
Are there possibilities that among these two string, one is empty, the other is not?
Should we just set them separately in the JSON?

No. The originatortype in the backend will always be initialized with a default enum value.

So we just have to check if originator Id is not empty (this means that the dump is user-trigerred) and then fill in the Json value

Please bump up the schema version here.

                "Originator": {
                    "description": "The source of the log entry.",
                    "longDescription": "This property shall contain the source of the log entry.",
                    "readonly": true,
                    "type": "string",
                    "versionAdded": "v1_11_0"
                },
                "OriginatorType": {
                    "$ref": "#/definitions/OriginatorTypes",
                    "description": "The type of originator data.",
                    "longDescription": "This property shall contain the type of originator data.",
                    "readonly": true,
                    "versionAdded": "v1_11_0"
                },
Done
Validator passed?
Yes, the redfish validator passed.
Need an update, as is would fail the validator

?  This is taking a dbus enum and loading it directly into a Redfish enum.  Surely that's not 1:1?  I would expect dbus enus to be something of the form of xyz.openbmc_project.OriginatorType.Foo, which definitely doesn't match redfish.
In method parseDumpEntryFromDbusObject:line 402 , these properties are fetched from the dbus. The property name used here is same name

> In method parseDumpEntryFromDbusObject:line 402 , these properties are fetched from the dbus. The property name used here is same name

Yes,in line 429 - the dbus enum will be fetched, type casted to string and then be assigned to "originatorType"
Right, of which OriginatorType is a Redfish Enum, not a string.  Can you please link the phosphor-dbus-interfaces review that you're working through?

+1. Even though https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/a1347418307d31a94bd21f22897aa508df938dcf/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Common/OriginatedBy.interface.yaml#L20 matches Redfish

       "OriginatorTypes": {
            "enum": [
                "Client",
                "Internal",
                "SupportingService"
            ],

we should still have a translateOriginatorTypeDbusToRedfish

At this level they don't match, becauese the dbus interface would be

xyz.openbmc_project.Common.OriginatedBy.Client
ect

which doesn't match Redfish.
Ack
So if we don't have a originator Id, we leave off the originiator Type, I guess that would exclude the defaults so I think this is fine.

Hi Reviewers, can you please vote for this change to get it merged?
Thanks
This doesn't directly map from dbus paths to redfish.  Some conversion will be required.

This "id" from the dbus is a plain string (as defined in the dbus-interfaces).

bmcweb just fetches it and sends it back to the redfish client (just like it is done in other places - eg: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/58688/9/redfish-core/lib/log_services.hpp#b1576)

Do you still think, a conversion on this string is needed?

You linked to message, which is a user facing string.

If I look at phosphor-debus-interfaces, the description is right in the string "This is an implementation-defined string"

In redfish, this is not implementation defined.  From the CSDL "This property shall contain the source of the log entry"

This means that the source of the log entry needs to be resolvable to something in the Redfish tree, otherwise what's the point?  Or am I missing something in my analysis there?

This Originator ID is implementation specific (as in the dbus-interfaces). For "dumps", the backend takes the client ID as the originatorID. It is stored as a plain string, and that is read back by bmcweb which is sent in the redfish response.
 
> This means that the source of the log entry needs to be resolvable to something in the Redfish tree
This plain string need not be converted to another string (redfish-compliant) right? Because, even in CSDL, the type is a string. Hope we dont have any validations for plain string.

This is for dump logentry.

If any other log entry happens to implement "OriginatedBy" interface to use this property and that stores some other unique id, then that can have its own implementation to interpret this string for redfish response.
It seems good to me. This is a string which need not have any conversions in this usecase.

> This Originator ID is implementation specific

Please quote the redfish spec (in a similar way as I have) that says that it's implementation specific.  That was not my reading.

As you have already quoted:
```
Originator:
          description: The source of the log entry.
          readOnly: true
          type: string
          x-longDescription: This property shall contain the source of the log entry.
```

For dumps, clientId is taken as the source string in the backend. Since redfish specifies "string" as its type, do we need any conversion in bmcweb for this plain string that is read from dbus?
Done

> This means that the source of the log entry needs to be resolvable to something in the Redfish tree, otherwise what's the point? Or am I missing something in my analysis there?

Then they would have done a link to an array of Redfish resources..

e.g. 
```
                "Originator": {
                    "description": "An array of links to resources or objects that .....",
                    "items": {
                        "$ref": "http://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/odata-v4.json#/definitions/idRef"
                    },
                    "longDescription": "This property shall contain an array of links to resources or objects that....",
                    "readonly": true,
                    "type": "array",
```

but they didn't (not sure I agree with them).. 
So https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/a1347418307d31a94bd21f22897aa508df938dcf/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Common/OriginatedBy.interface.yaml#L8 seems to map closest with what they did
Hi @Ed, this seems reasonable to me as well. Can this get merged please? Thanks.
Per the pattern we use elsewhere, please put this code in its own method.
Done
Per the developing guide.  WHY is this useful?  What information is put into originator?  (considering it's implementation defined, we need to document it.)
Ack
Seems reasonable to me
Hi Maintainers, Can this commit go in?
Please use the generated redfish enums for this.
Done

We're now persisting the clients IP, which is generally considered as identifying information, which imposes a new set of requirements on bmcweb that we generally haven't in the past.

It also isn't mentioned at all in the commit message.  What guarantees at an interface level do we have that the daemon on the other end supports this?  Have all the daemons been tested?

I have updated the commit message indicating that client's/dump originator's ip address will be stored in the redfish property and the same will be stored in the backend that already has this support.
So we default to Internal, 🤷 seems okay.
